cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper uses a deep learning approach to detect and localize inner ears in head CT scans, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of false positive suppression and shape-based constraints also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could potentially fall under the neural engineering (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
